{
  "texts": [
    "In the case of isotropic CTMRG, all CTMs are identical, simplifying the contraction process.",
    "The transfer matrix T horiz along the horizontal direction is constructed using the up and down MPS tensors.",
    "For anisotropic CTMRG, however, the full unit cell must be considered, requiring the contraction of all up and down MPS tensors, as illustrated in the figure.",
    "Similarly one can construct the transfer matrix long the vertical direction using left and right MPS tensors.In the CTMRG framework, free energy (per site), observables and correlation functions can be directly computed from the CTMs and MPS tensors; we refer to Refs.",
    "[7,10,11] for further details."
  ]
}